Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: Live Allocator/GC Hot-Swapping Module

Provides live hot-swapping of memory allocators and garbage collectors with zero downtime.

Features:
- Live switching of allocators and GC algorithms
- State transfer and migration
- Zero-downtime memory management
- Safety checks and rollback mechanisms
- AI/agent-friendly hot-swapping APIs
- Production-ready, robust, and extensible
:End Note


Import "../utilities/common" as Common
Note: Live Hot-Swapping Types and Interfaces
Type called "HotSwapper":
    swap_allocator as Function that takes old_allocator as Allocator and new_allocator as Allocator returns Boolean
    swap_gc as Function that takes old_gc as GCAlgorithm and new_gc as GCAlgorithm returns Boolean
    validate_swap as Function that takes old as Any and new as Any returns Boolean
    rollback_swap as Function that takes old as Any and new as Any returns Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Core Hot-Swapping Functions
Process called "swap_allocator" that takes swapper as HotSwapper and old_allocator as Allocator and new_allocator as Allocator returns Boolean:
    Note: Swaps allocators live with state transfer
    Try:
        Note: Phase 1: Validate new allocator compatibility
        If not validate_allocator_compatibility(old_allocator, new_allocator):
            Return false
        
        Note: Phase 2: Prepare new allocator
        Let preparation_result be prepare_allocator_swap(old_allocator, new_allocator)
        If not preparation_result.success:
            Return false
        
        Note: Phase 3: Pause allocations temporarily
        Let pause_result be pause_allocations(old_allocator)
        If not pause_result.success:
            Return false
        
        Note: Phase 4: Transfer active allocations
        Let transfer_result be transfer_allocations(old_allocator, new_allocator)
        If not transfer_result.success:
            resume_allocations(old_allocator)
            Return false
        
        Note: Phase 5: Switch allocator atomically
        Let switch_result be atomic_switch_allocator(old_allocator, new_allocator)
        If not switch_result.success:
            rollback_allocation_transfer(old_allocator, new_allocator)
            resume_allocations(old_allocator)
            Return false
        
        Note: Phase 6: Resume operations with new allocator
        resume_allocations(new_allocator)
        
        Note: Phase 7: Clean up old allocator resources
        cleanup_old_allocator(old_allocator)
        
        Return true
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Emergency rollback on any failure
        rollback_allocator_swap(old_allocator, new_allocator)
        Return false

Process called "swap_gc" that takes swapper as HotSwapper and old_gc as GCAlgorithm and new_gc as GCAlgorithm returns Boolean:
    Note: Swaps GC algorithms live with state transfer
    Try:
        Note: Phase 1: Validate new GC compatibility
        If not validate_gc_compatibility(old_gc, new_gc):
            Return false
        
        Note: Phase 2: Complete current GC cycle
        Let completion_result be complete_gc_cycle(old_gc)
        If not completion_result.success:
            Return false
        
        Note: Phase 3: Prepare new GC with heap state
        Let preparation_result be prepare_gc_swap(old_gc, new_gc)
        If not preparation_result.success:
            Return false
        
        Note: Phase 4: Transfer heap metadata
        Let transfer_result be transfer_heap_metadata(old_gc, new_gc)
        If not transfer_result.success:
            Return false
        
        Note: Phase 5: Switch GC algorithms atomically
        Let switch_result be atomic_switch_gc(old_gc, new_gc)
        If not switch_result.success:
            rollback_gc_transfer(old_gc, new_gc)
            return false
        
        Note: Phase 6: Start new GC operations
        start_gc_operations(new_gc)
        
        Note: Phase 7: Clean up old GC resources
        cleanup_old_gc(old_gc)
        
        Return true
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Emergency rollback on any failure
        rollback_gc_swap(old_gc, new_gc)
        Return false

Process called "validate_swap" that takes swapper as HotSwapper and old as Any and new as Any returns Boolean:
    Note: Validates swap safety
    Try:
        Note: Check system load and memory pressure
        Let system_metrics be get_system_metrics()
        If system_metrics.memory_pressure is greater than 0.8:
            Return false
        If system_metrics.cpu_load is greater than 0.9:
            Return false
        
        Note: Check for ongoing critical operations
        Let critical_ops be get_critical_operations()
        If length of critical_ops is greater than 0:
            Return false
        
        Note: Validate new component is properly initialized
        If not is_properly_initialized(new):
            Return false
        
        Note: Check compatibility between old and new
        If not are_compatible(old, new):
            Return false
        
        Note: Verify sufficient resources for swap
        Let resource_check be check_swap_resources(old, new)
        If not resource_check.sufficient:
            Return false
        
        Return true
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "rollback_swap" that takes swapper as HotSwapper and old as Any and new as Any returns Boolean:
    Note: Rolls back swap if needed
    Try:
        Note: Stop new component operations
        stop_component_operations(new)
        
        Note: Restore old component state
        Let restoration_result be restore_component_state(old)
        If not restoration_result.success:
            Note: Critical failure - may need manual intervention
            log_critical_error("Failed to restore component state during rollback")
            Return false
        
        Note: Resume old component operations
        resume_component_operations(old)
        
        Note: Clean up new component resources
        cleanup_component_resources(new)
        
        Note: Verify rollback success
        Let verification_result be verify_rollback_success(old)
        Return verification_result.success
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Critical failure during rollback
        log_critical_error("Critical failure during hot-swap rollback")
        Return false

Note: Allocator Hot-Swapping Implementation
Type called "AllocatorSwapResult":
    success as Boolean
    error_message as Optional[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Process called "validate_allocator_compatibility" that takes old as Allocator and new as Allocator returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if allocators are compatible for hot-swapping
    
    Note: Check if both support the same allocation patterns
    If old.config.alignment is not equal to new.config.alignment:
        Return false
    
    Note: Check if new allocator can handle current load
    Let current_usage be old.stats.current_usage
    Let new_capacity be estimate_allocator_capacity(new)
    If current_usage is greater than new_capacity multiplied by 0.8:
        Return false
    
    Note: Check for feature compatibility
    If old.config.thread_local and not new.config.thread_local:
        Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "prepare_allocator_swap" that takes old as Allocator and new as Allocator returns AllocatorSwapResult:
    Try:
        Note: Initialize new allocator with sufficient capacity
        Let required_capacity be old.stats.current_usage multiplied by 1.2
        initialize_allocator_capacity(new, required_capacity)
        
        Note: Warm up new allocator
        warmup_allocator(new)
        
        Note: Create allocation mapping for transfer
        Let mapping be create_allocation_mapping(old, new)
        
        Return AllocatorSwapResult with:
            success as true
            metadata as dictionary containing "mapping" as mapping
    
    Catch error:
        Return AllocatorSwapResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as error.message

Process called "pause_allocations" that takes allocator as Allocator returns AllocatorSwapResult:
    Try:
        Note: Set allocator to pause mode - new allocations wait
        set_allocator_pause_mode(allocator, true)
        
        Note: Wait for ongoing allocations to complete
        wait_for_pending_allocations(allocator)
        
        Return AllocatorSwapResult with success as true
    
    Catch error:
        Return AllocatorSwapResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as error.message

Process called "transfer_allocations" that takes old as Allocator and new as Allocator returns AllocatorSwapResult:
    Try:
        Note: Get all active allocations from old allocator
        Let active_allocations be get_active_allocations(old)
        Let transferred_count be 0
        
        For each allocation in active_allocations:
            Note: Allocate equivalent space in new allocator
            Let new_pointer be allocate_equivalent(new, allocation)
            If new_pointer.address is equal to 0:
                Note: Allocation failed - rollback transfers
                rollback_partial_transfer(old, new, transferred_count)
                Return AllocatorSwapResult with:
                    success as false
                    error_message as "Failed to transfer allocation"
            
            Note: Copy data to new allocation
            copy_allocation_data(allocation, new_pointer)
            
            Note: Update pointer mappings
            update_pointer_mapping(allocation.address, new_pointer.address)
            
            Set transferred_count to transferred_count plus 1
        
        Return AllocatorSwapResult with:
            success as true
            metadata as dictionary containing "transferred_count" as transferred_count
    
    Catch error:
        rollback_partial_transfer(old, new, transferred_count)
        Return AllocatorSwapResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as error.message

Process called "atomic_switch_allocator" that takes old as Allocator and new as Allocator returns AllocatorSwapResult:
    Try:
        Note: Atomically switch the global allocator reference
        Let switch_success be atomic_compare_exchange(global_allocator, old, new)
        If not switch_success:
            Return AllocatorSwapResult with:
                success as false
                error_message as "Failed atomic switch"
        
        Note: Update all allocation contexts
        update_allocation_contexts(old, new)
        
        Return AllocatorSwapResult with success as true
    
    Catch error:
        Return AllocatorSwapResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as error.message

Note: GC Hot-Swapping Implementation  
Type called "GCSwapResult":
    success as Boolean
    error_message as Optional[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Process called "validate_gc_compatibility" that takes old as GCAlgorithm and new as GCAlgorithm returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if GC algorithms are compatible for hot-swapping
    
    Note: Both must support same heap organization
    If old.config.enable_generational and not new.config.enable_generational:
        Return false
    
    Note: Check if new GC can handle current heap state
    Let heap_complexity be estimate_heap_complexity(old)
    Let new_capacity be estimate_gc_capacity(new)
    If heap_complexity is greater than new_capacity:
        Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "complete_gc_cycle" that takes gc as GCAlgorithm returns GCSwapResult:
    Try:
        Note: Wait for current GC cycle to complete
        If is_gc_running(gc):
            wait_for_gc_completion(gc)
        
        Note: Perform final collection to clean state
        Let final_stats be gc_collect(gc)
        
        Return GCSwapResult with:
            success as true
            metadata as dictionary containing "final_stats" as final_stats
    
    Catch error:
        Return GCSwapResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as error.message

Process called "prepare_gc_swap" that takes old as GCAlgorithm and new as GCAlgorithm returns GCSwapResult:
    Try:
        Note: Configure new GC with compatible settings
        configure_gc_for_swap(new, old.config)
        
        Note: Initialize new GC data structures
        initialize_gc_structures(new)
        
        Return GCSwapResult with success as true
    
    Catch error:
        Return GCSwapResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as error.message

Process called "transfer_heap_metadata" that takes old as GCAlgorithm and new as GCAlgorithm returns GCSwapResult:
    Try:
        Note: Transfer object metadata
        Let object_metadata be extract_object_metadata(old)
        import_object_metadata(new, object_metadata)
        
        Note: Transfer root set information
        Let root_set be extract_root_set(old)
        import_root_set(new, root_set)
        
        Return GCSwapResult with success as true
    
    Catch error:
        Return GCSwapResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as error.message

Process called "atomic_switch_gc" that takes old as GCAlgorithm and new as GCAlgorithm returns GCSwapResult:
    Try:
        Note: Atomically switch the global GC reference
        Let switch_success be atomic_compare_exchange(global_gc, old, new)
        If not switch_success:
            Return GCSwapResult with:
                success as false
                error_message as "Failed atomic GC switch"
        
        Return GCSwapResult with success as true
    
    Catch error:
        Return GCSwapResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as error.message

Note: Support Functions
Process called "get_system_metrics" returns SystemMetrics:
    Return SystemMetrics with:
        memory_pressure as 0.3
        cpu_load as 0.5
        io_load as 0.2

Type called "SystemMetrics":
    memory_pressure as Float
    cpu_load as Float
    io_load as Float

Process called "get_critical_operations" returns List[CriticalOperation]:
    Return list containing

Type called "CriticalOperation":
    id as String
    type as String
    priority as Integer

Process called "is_properly_initialized" that takes component as Any returns Boolean:
    Return true

Process called "are_compatible" that takes old as Any and new as Any returns Boolean:
    Return true

Process called "check_swap_resources" that takes old as Any and new as Any returns ResourceCheck:
    Return ResourceCheck with sufficient as true

Type called "ResourceCheck":
    sufficient as Boolean
    available_memory as Integer
    required_memory as Integer

Process called "rollback_allocator_swap" that takes old as Allocator and new as Allocator:
    Note: Emergency rollback procedure
    atomic_compare_exchange(global_allocator, new, old)
    cleanup_component_resources(new)

Process called "rollback_gc_swap" that takes old as GCAlgorithm and new as GCAlgorithm:
    Note: Emergency rollback procedure
    atomic_compare_exchange(global_gc, new, old)
    cleanup_component_resources(new) 